Germany’s Fuchs Says Countries Should Sell Gold, WiWo Reports

-- B y   R a g n h i l d   K j e t l a n d
-- 
2011-08-28T11:24:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-28/germany-s-fuchs-says-countries-should-sell-gold-wiwo-reports.html
Michael Fuchs , the  Christian
Democratic Union ’s deputy leader in  Germany ’s parliament, said
the southern European “crisis countries” should sell part of
their  gold reserves ,  WirtschaftsWoche  reported.  With the proceeds, the countries should then buy back their
own “weakening” government bonds, the magazine cited him as
saying, according to an e-mailed preview of an article that will
appear in tomorrow’s edition.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ragnhild Kjetland in Frankfurt at 
 rkjetland@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Kenneth Wong  in Berlin at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  